text: Est is a town in the Dutch province of Gelderland. It is a part of the municipality of West Betuwe, and lies about 8 km west of Tiel. In 2018, the town of Est had 578+ inhabitants. The built-up area of the town was 0.065 km², and contained 108 residences.Statistics Netherlands (CBS), Bevolkingskernen in Nederland 2001. (Statistics are for the continuous built-up area). The statistical area "Est", which also can include the peripheral parts of the village, as well as the surrounding countryside, has a population of around 610.Statistics Netherlands (CBS), Statline: Kerncijfers wijken en buurten 2003-2005 .
